<HEADLINE> IFC Increase Borrowing in Global Hong Kong Dollars </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, October 10 (Xinhua) -- The International Finance
Corporation (IFC) today announced the increase of the 400 million
Hong Kong dollar issue by an additional 100 million HK dollars,
which is about 13 million U.S. dollars, to a total of 500 million
HK dollars.
</P>
<P>
The terms remain the same as the original issue, which has a
semi-annual coupon of 7.05 percent per annum, and a maturity of
three years.
</P>
<P>
The proceeds of the increase will be also swapped into U.S.
dollar floating rate funds.
</P>
<P>
The latest transaction will bring the IFC's market borrowing to
about 1,265 million dollars equivalent for the fiscal year 1998,
which began on June 19, 1997.
</P>
<P>
The IFC is a member of the World Bank Group and the largest
multilateral source of financing for private sector projects in
developing countries. 
</P>
</TEXT>
