<DATE_TIME> 1997-10-11 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Local Elections in Mozambique to Be Postponed to </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>

<P>
Next April
</P>
<P>
MAPUTO, October 10 (Xinhua) -- Mozambican Minister of State
Administration Alfredo Gamito said here today that it is not
possible to hold the first local elections in Mozambique before
next April.
</P>
<P>
He told reporters that a lot of preparation work for the
local elections cannot be finished until the end of the first
week of April next year.
</P>
<P>
The local elections were originally scheduled to take place
on December 27 this year. As the money for the elections promised
by international community has not been put in place, the
registration of voters was not implemented as planned for August
18 to September 5. 
</P>
</TEXT>
