<HEADLINE> China, Kuwait Deadlocked 1-1 at Halftime </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUWAIT, October 10 (Xinhua) -- China and Kuwait played to 1-1
at halftime at a crucial match of the Asian World Cup soccer
qualification tournament here on Friday.
</P>
<P>
At the third minute, China's top striker Hao Haidong blasted
the ball into the left corner of the net with turnaround shot
after connecting a pass at the top of the penalty box.
</P>
<P>
Chinese goalkeeper Ou Chuliang then made several brilliant
saves including the one he palmed out a close shot by unmarked
Esam M. Sakeen.
</P>
<P>
At the 25th minute, Jassem M. Houwaidi netted his third goal in
his fourth match, putting the score at one-all.
</P>
<P>
Houwaidi lobbed the ball into an open net as Ou ran out in a
desperate attempt to dispossess the Kuwaiti top striker. 
</P>
</TEXT>
