<HEADLINE> UK Hails Anti-Landmines Campaign Winning Nobel Prize </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, October 10 (Xinhua) -- British Foreign Secretary Robin
Cook said here today that the British government was delighted
that the Nobel Peace Prize had been awarded to the anti-landmines
campaign.
</P>
<P>
"I am delighted by the news that the Nobel Peace Prize has been
awarded to the International Campaign to Ban Landmines," Cook said
in a statement issued this afternoon.
</P>
<P>
"This is a fitting tribute to the part played by
non-governmental organizations in the worldwide struggle against
the humanitarian tragedy caused by anti-personnel landmines," he
said.
</P>
<P>
He stressed that the London government "has played an active
part in this struggle, both in negotiating an international
agreement to ban anti-personnel landmines and in helping to
alleviate the sufferings of the victims." 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
