<HEADLINE> S. Africa, India Negotiate About Arms Deal </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JOHANNESBURG, October 10 (Xinhua) -- South Africa is
negotiating with India about sales of gun turrets to India for
its tanks in what could be the country's biggest arms sale.
</P>
<P>
An Indian official, who is member of Indian Prime Minister
Inder Gujral's delegation in the country, said South Africa is
one of the countries competing for the deal.
</P>
<P>
Southern African Broadcasting Association today quoted the
official as saying that negotiations between India and South
Africa are at an early stage.
</P>
<P>
The deal could be worth about five billion U.S. Dollars, the
Indian official said.
</P>
<P>
Gujral is in South Africa for an official visit.
</P>
<P>
South African Deputy Foreign Minister Aziz Pahad has confirmed
defense deals between the two sides could be in the offing.
</P>
<P>
But officials in the ministries of Defense and Foreign Affairs
have denied any deals are being negotiated. 
</P>
