<DATE_TIME> 1997-10-11 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China Beats Kuwait 2-1 in World Cup Qualifier </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUWAIT, October 10 (Xinhua) -- China beat Kuwait 2-1 in the
dying minutes at a crucial game of the Asian World Cup soccer
qualifying tournament here Friday night.
</P>
<P>
With just two minutes left, Chinese forward Gao Feng dribbled
into the penalty box and left-footed the ball into the net for the
winner.
</P>
<P>
Chinese head coach Qi Wusheng fielded Gao, known for speed and
calmness, with 17 minutes left in the second half as Kuwaiti
players looked jaded.
</P>
<P>
China, which had snatched three wins and one draw in their
previous seven encounters with Kuwait, opened the scoring through
its top striker Hao Haidong three minutes into action.
</P>
<P>
Hao, who has been troubled by a fever, blasted the ball into
the left corner of the net with a turnaround shot after connecting
a pass at the top of the penalty box.
</P>
<P>
Chinese goalkeeper Ou Chuliang then made several brilliant
saves including the one he palmed out a close shot by unmarked
Esam M. Sakeen.
</P>
<P>
At the 25th minute, Jassem M. Houwaidi netted his third goal in
his fourth match, putting the score at one-all.
</P>
<P>
Houwaidi lobbed the ball into an open net as Ou ran out in a
desperate attempt to dispossess the Kuwaiti top striker.
</P>
<P>
China now places second in the five-team group A in which the
winner goes to the French finals and the second-finisher vies for
a berth with Group B runner-up.
</P>
<P>
The loser in the clash of the runner-ups fight for a remaining
spot with Australia.
</P>
<P>
Iran, which has posted two wins and as many draws, topped the
group with eight points, just one point over China which recorded
two wins, one draw and one loss.
</P>
<P>
Saudi Arabia, which will plays its fourth game against Qatar on
Saturday, placed third with four points. Kuwait fell to fourth
with four points.
</P>
<P>
Qatar, which has only won one point from a draw with China, was
last. 
</P>
</TEXT>
