<HEADLINE> China Ratifies Protocols on Africa's Being </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ADDIS ABABA, October 10 (Xinhua) -- Chinese Ambassador Jiang
Zhengyun today handed the "Instrument of Ratification" on two
protocols to the African Nuclear-Weapon-Free-Zone Treaty to OAU
Secretary General Salim Ahmed Salim.
</P>
<P>
The "Instrument of Ratification" was signed by Chinese
President Jiang Zemin.
</P>
<P>
It said, "in accordance with the decision made by the standing
committee of the eighth National People's Congress at its 26th
session", the Chinese President "ratifies protocol I and protocol
II to the African Nuclear-Weapon-Free-Zone Treaty signed by Mr.
Li Zhaoxing, representative of the government of the People's
Republic of China in Cairo on April 11, 1996."
</P>
<P>
"The People's Republic of China enforces the full observance
of all enshrined in the afore-mentioned protocols," it added.
</P>
<P>
Upon receiving the "Instrument of Ratification", Salim
expressed his welcome and appreciation to China's ratification of
the two protocols, saying this demonstrated the commitment of the
Chinese government's support for the initiatives of Africa and
the Organization of African Unity (OAU).
</P>
<P>
It also indicated China's desire to further develop the
friendly cooperation relations with Africa and the OAU, he added.
</P>
<P>
Salim pointed out that the declaration of the African Nuclear-
Weapon-Free-Zone is a contribution to the elimination of the
nuclear threat and China's support is very important for
realizing this goal.
</P>
<P>
Salim asked the Chinese ambassador to convey his appreciation
to Jiang and the Chinese government.
</P>
<P>
The African Nuclear-Weapon-Free-Zone Treaty was adopted by the
62nd ordinary session of the OAU council of ministers and
endorsed by the 31st session of the assembly of heads of state
and government in June, 1995. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
