<HEADLINE> Cholera Kills 53 in C. Tanzanian Region </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DAR ES SALAAM, October 10 (Xinhua) -- Cholera has killed 53
people in the Dodoma region in central Tanzania, a local medical
official said.
</P>
<P>
Of the dead, 28 were reported in the Dodoma municipality, 21
in Dodoma rural area, three in Kongwa and one in Mpawa, said Dr.
Meshack Masi today.
</P>
<P>
Although the region has sufficient medicines to contain the
contagious disease, a total of 525 cases have been reported
during the period.
</P>
<P>
Dr. Masi said until today, six victims are still under
treatment in hospitals.
</P>
<P>
Masi appealed to local residents to boil water, most of which
was contaminated, and to observe general hygienic regulations,
such as cleaning their surroundings. 
</P>
</TEXT>
