<HEADLINE> DPRK Celebrates Kim's Election As Party Chief </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PYONGYANG, October 11 (Xinhua) -- A grand rally was held in
Pyongyang today to celebrate Kim Jong Il's election as general
secretary of the Workers' Party of Korea (WPK).
</P>
<P>
Up to 300,000 people from all walks of life in the capital of
the Democratic People's Republic of Korea (DPRK) gathered at the
Kim Il Song Square and the two banks of the Dae Dong Gang River
this afternoon.
</P>
<P>
The celebration was attended by many high-ranking party and
government officials including Ri Jong Ok and Pak Song Chul,
vice-presidents of the DPRK, and Foreign Minister Kim Yong Nam.
</P>
<P>
Huge portraits of the late WPK chief Kim Il Song and current
WPK chief Kim Jong Il stood in the middle of the Kim Il Song
Square.
</P>
<P>
Placards near the portraits said, "Long Live Great Leader Kim
Il Song," "Long Live the Glorious Workers' Party of Korea," and
"Warmly Congratulating Great Leader Kim Jong Il on Election as
General Secretary of Our Party."
</P>
<P>
Kim Jong Il was formally named as the WPK general secretary on
Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
Addressing the celebration, Kang Hyan Su, chairman of the
Pyongyang Municipal People's Committee, said that Comrade Kim Jong
Il's election as general secretary of the WPK is a historic event,
which showed the common will and aspiration of all WPK members,
officers and soldiers of the Korean People's Army (KPA), as well
as all DPRK people.
</P>
<P>
As Kang Hyan Su expressed the warmest congratulations to Kim
Jong Il in the name of all WPK members and people of Pyongyang,
countless colorful balloons were flying over the square.
</P>
<P>
Kang Hyan Su said, "Let us rally closely around the WPK Central
Committee headed by Comrade Kim Jong Il to strive harder for the
reunification of the fatherland and the accomplishment of our
major cause."
</P>
<P>
Finally, a message of congratulation was passed and sent to
Comrade Kim Jong Il in the name of all the participants at the
rally.
</P>
<P>
Also today another grand celebration was held by the Korean
People's Army in Pyongyang to mark Kim's election as general
secretary of the WPK.
</P>
<P>
Jo Myong Rok, director of the general political bureau of the
KPA, and Kim Yong Chun, chief of the general of staff of the KPA,
attended the celebration.
</P>
<P>
Jo Myong Rok said at the meeting that Comrade Kim Jong Il's
election as general secretary of the WPK is supported by the whole
party, army and people.
</P>
<P>
Recently, various activities were staged in Pyongyang and the
other parts of the country to celebrate Kim's election as the
WPK's general secretary. 
</P>
</TEXT>
