<HEADLINE> Xinhua World News Summary at 1500 GMT, October 11 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JERUSALEM -- A large demonstration was held Saturday in the
West Bank city of Ramallah in protest against the Israeli
prevention of an independent Palestinian state.
</P>
<P>
About 1,500 Palestinians participated in the demonstration at
the main Manara Square of Ramallah, which was organized by the
Fatah Youth Organization, a reliable Palestinian source said.
</P>
<P>
During the demonstration which lasted about two hours, the
organizers strongly criticized Israel for preventing the
Palestinian people to establish an independent
state. (Israel-Demonstration)
</P>
