President Wan Muhamad Nor Matha, Senate Speaker Meechai Ruchupan,
Constitution Drafting Assembly Chairman Uthai Pimchaichon and
opposition leader Chuan Leekpai attended the signing ceremony held
 at the palace. (Thailand-Charter)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
BUENOS AIRES -- All 74 people on board an Argentine DC-9 that
crashed in western Uruguay died in the accident, an Argentine air
force statement said Saturday.
</P>
<P>
The wreckage of the twin-engine airliner, which crashed late
Friday in a swampy, hilly area outside the Uruguayan border town
of Fray Bentos, is spread over a vast area of rough terrain, it
said.
</P>
<P>
The Argentine domestic airliner, carrying 69 passengers and
five crew members, crashed at 11 p.m. local time when trying to
avoid a heavy storm. (Uruguay-Crash-Toll)
</P>
