<HEADLINE> Uzbekstan draws Japan 1-1 in World Cup Qualifier </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TASHKENT, October 11 (Xinhua) -- Uzbekstan forced Japan a 1-1
draw in the World Cup Asian Group B qualifier on Saturday.
</P>
<P>
Uzbek Bahtiyor Qambaraliyev scored in the 31st minute by his
powerful shot from outside the area.
</P>
<P>
Uzbekstan took the lead until 88th minute when Japanese Masami
Ihara's long through-ball from the midfield was missed by Uzbek
goal keeper Pavel Bugalo and rolled into the net.
</P>
<P>
The Japanese now have six points from one win, three draws and
one defeat, seven points behind South Korea and one less than the
United Arab Emirates. They are in grave danger of missing a berth
in France.
</P>
<P>
Uzbekistan, the 1994 Asian Games gold winners, have two draws
and three defeats for two points at bottom of the five-nation
round robin.
</P>
<P>
Kazakhstan and South Korea drew 1-1 in Almaty Saturday.
</P>
<P>
The winners of the group automatically advance to the finals
and the runners-up will take on second placers of Group A, while
the losers of the playoff will play Australia in the last
playoff. 
</P>
