<HEADLINE> Official Urges Conscientious Donations </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DALIAN, October 11 (Xinhua) -- Local governments should learn
from Dalian and conscientiously donate to society by the year
2,000, according to Fan Baojun, vice-minister of civil affairs.
</P>
<P>
During a meeting focusing on ways to offer frequent financial
and material assistance, Fan proposed that China should establish
a relatively complete system in developed cities by the year 2000
to promote donations. Fan said the system should include working
organizations and equipment, and should be based on community
organizations.
</P>
<P>
Fan pointed to Dalian's experience of using available community
service resources to reduce costs and improve community services.
</P>
<P>
He also called for the combination of routine donation work
with large-scale donation drives.
</P>
<P>
The donations are made to help those in difficulties,
especially in poverty-stricken areas. 
</P>
