<HEADLINE> Stress on Environmental Protection Laws </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DALIAN, October 11 (Xinhua) -- State Councillor Song Jian today
called for expanded implementation of environmental protection
laws and regulations to ensure a better environment for the 21st
century.
</P>
<P>
Legislative bodies at various levels have introduced a
framework of laws and regulations on environmental protection over
the past two decades. However, the key lies in enforcement,
according to Song, head of the State Council Environmental
Protection Committee.
</P>
<P>
Those responsible for environmental pollution and ecological
damages must be subject to severe penalties in accordance with the
laws and regulations, said Song.
</P>
<P>
Environmental protection departments, which are both
administrative and enforcement agencies, must justly and
forcefully combat illegal activities, said Song.
</P>
<P>
Song also noted the need to enhance general public awareness of
laws and regulations concerning environmental protection.  
</P>
