<HEADLINE> Gore: Jiang's Visit Important Turning Point </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, October 10 (Xinhua) -- U.S. Vice President Al Gore
said here today that the upcoming state visit to the United States
of Chinese President Jiang Zemin will be an important turning
point in the American-Chinese relations.
</P>
<P>
Jiang's visit, scheduled for the end of this month, is a
significant event in the relationship between the U.S. and China
and will mark an important turning point for furthering bilateral
ties, Gore told a visiting Chinese official at the White House.
</P>
<P>
Liu Huaqiu, director of the Office of Foreign Affairs under the
State Council of China, arrived here Wednesday in preparation for
Jiang's visit, the first in 12 years by a Chinese head of state to
the United States.
</P>
<P>
Gore told Liu that he will join President Bill Clinton in talks
with Jiang in Washington later this month, and he himself will
host a luncheon in Jiang's honor.
</P>
<P>
He is optimistic about the prospect of cooperation between the
two countries in energy and environment, believing that the
upcoming American-Chinese summit will help expand the cooperation.
</P>
<P>
Liu, who have met with President Clinton, House Speaker Newt
Gingrich, Secretary of Defense William S. Cohen and President's
National Security Advisor Samuel Berger in the past two days,
shared the belief that Jiang's visit is historically important and
will definitely usher the bilateral ties into a new era of
development.
</P>
<P>
Liu also met with Secretary of State Madeline Albright this
afternoon. She said that the preparatory work for Jiang's visit
has been going smoothly thanks to the joint efforts by both sides.
</P>
<P>
She said the Americans are looking forward to the "important
summit meeting" between Clinton and Jiang, which she believes will
be the focus of world attention.
</P>
<P>
She thanked the Chinese side for the "warm and friendly"
reception accorded to her during her trip to China last February.
She said that China's development and changes for the better left
her an "unforgettable impression."
</P>
<P>
Liu said that Jiang's visit is not only important for better
Sino-American relations but also conducive to the peace and
stability in the Asian-Pacific region and the world as a whole.
</P>
</TEXT>
