<HEADLINE> Iran Launches Victory-8 Maneuvers in Persian Gulf </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TEHRAN, October 11 (Xinhua) -- Iran's military forces
launched large-scale war games in a 50,000 sq-km area from
Lavan Island in the northern section of the Persian Gulf up
to the Kuwait border this morning.
</P>
<P>
Iran's official news agency IRNA reported that the Victory-8
is being jointly carried by the army and the Islamic
Revolution Guards Corps (IRGC).
</P>
<P>
Morteza Safari, commander of the maneuver's joint headquarters,
said the 5-stage war games is staged to exercise offensive
tactics against hypothetical enemy and safeguarding naval interests
and resources of Iran in the Persian Gulf.
</P>
<P>
Units of the Naval, Air and Ground forces as well as
IRGC's air and naval units will take part in the maneuver,
he said.
</P>
<P>
The commander said that 50 vessels, destroyers, submarines,
missile vessels, 100 speed gunboats, over 18 aircraft and 20
helicopters will be deployed in the military exercise, he
added.
</P>
<P>
The war games would also employ two Russian-made submarines,
new communication systems and missiles and would exercise electronic
wars as well as discovering and defending against mines.
</P>
<P>
However, he did not specify how many forces will be
involved in the war games. 
</P>
</TEXT>
