<TEXT>
<P>
ADDIS ABABA, October 11 (Xinhua) -- Experts from African
countries are to meet in Addis Ababa from october 23-24 to
brainstorm on an input to the upcoming Tokyo Conference on
African Development due to be held in October or November 1998.
</P>
<P>
A press release from the United Nations Economic Commission
for Africa (ECA) said today it would assist African governments
in preparing for the Tokyo preparatory meeting from November
10-11.
