Executive Secretary, agreed to a request from the government of
Japan that the ECA join the preparatory committee for 1998
meeting.
</P>
<P>
The Tokyo conference organized by Japan, the United Nations
and the Global Coalition for Africa, is a non-pledging
conference, intended to review progress made since the last
conference in 1993 and to produce action-oriented results.
</P>
<P>
Its overall goal is to strengthen the new, positive trends in
African development, including political and economic reforms,
regional cooperation and integration, and African ownership of
development initiative. the Global Coalition for Africa. 
