<HEADLINE> Series of History of Chinese Drama Published </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
FUZHOU, October 11 (Xinhua) -- The three-volume History of
Ancient and Modern Chinese Drama published by the Higher Education
Press in south China's Guangdong Province is now available to both
Chinese and foreign readers.
</P>
<P>
Publication of the series was announced today at a news
conference in Fuzhou, capital of east China's Fujian Province.
</P>
<P>
Li Wanjun, a professor with the Play Research Institute at
Fujian Normal University, served as chief compiler of the series.
</P>
<P>
The magnificent series, which covers events from ancient times
to 1996, contains an estimated two million Chinese characters.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
