<HEADLINE> Kiefer, Gustafsson Advance to Singapore Open Final </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SINGAPORE, October 11 (Xinhua) -- Nicolas Kiefer rallied to a
6-7 (1-7), 6-3, 6-3 win over Swede Mikael Tillstrom on Saturday in
the Singapore Open tennis tournament.
</P>
<P>
The German will face Swede Magnus Gustafsson in Sunday's final.
</P>
<P>
Eight-seeded Kiefer sprained his right wrist late in the first
set and then lose the ensuing tiebreak 1-7 easily.
</P>
<P>
But Kiefer, who won his first ATP tour title in Toulouse two
weeks ago, overcame the pain to break Tillstrom's service twice in
the second set to draw level. His 14 aces helped him en route to
the victory.
</P>
<P>
But the wrist injury was serious enough to force the Germen and
his partner Alex Radulescu to quit their doubles semifinal against
Americans Jonathan Stark and Rick Leach, who received a walkover.
</P>
<P>
Stark and Leach will face the winners of the second semifinal
between Mahesh Bhupathi and Leander Paes of India and Tillstrom
and his compatriot Niklas Kulti.
</P>
<P>
Tillstrom's compatriot Gustafsson, who lost to Jim Courier in
the China Open last week, tried to rebuild a career interrupted by
injury. He norrowly beat another Swede Thomas Johansson 7-6 (7-5),
4-6, 7-6 (10-8) to snatch the final berth. 
</P>
</TEXT>
