<HEADLINE> Chinese General Calls for Implementation of Army Regulations </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, October 11 (Xinhua) -- Chinese General Fu Quanyou
today called for the conscientious study and implementation of
four revised regulations of the People's Liberation Army (PLA).
</P>
<P>
The regulations, which concern interior service, discipline,
formations, drills and garrisons, were put into effect a few days
ago under orders from President Jiang Zemin, who also serves as
chairman of the Central Military Commission.
</P>
<P>
The regulations, which are important measures designed to
manage the army in accordance with the new situation and efforts
to build the army, will promote modernization and standardization,
said Fu, member of the Central Military Commission and chief of
the general staff of the PLA.
</P>
<P>
He urged officers and soldiers to uphold the Chinese Communist
Party's absolute leadership in the army, and called on them to
dedicate themselves to their duties and intensify various orders
and discipline.
</P>
<P>
Fu made the remarks during a teleconference sponsored by the
Headquarters of the General Staff, the General Political
Department, and the General Logistics Department of the
PLA. 
