<HEADLINE> Palestinians Hold Demonstration in Ramallah </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JERUSALEM, October 11 (Xinhua) -- A large demonstration was held
today in the West bank city of Ramallah in protest against the
Israeli prevention of an independent Palestinian state.
</P>
<P>
About 1,500 Palestinians participated in the demonstration at
the main Manara Square of Ramallah, which was organized by
the Fatah Youth Organization, a reliable Palestinian source said.
</P>
<P>
During the demonstration which lasted about two hours, the
organizers strongly criticized Israel for preventing the
Palestinian people to establish an independent state.
</P>
<P>
The demonstrators also criticized Israel for its continuous
occupation of the Palestinian territories, and urged Israel to
end its closure as soon as possible.
</P>
<P>
Israel imposed total closures on Palestinian territories early
August following the bombing blasts in Jerusalem and the closure
has been strengthened since another bombing incident in Jerusalem
early September.
</P>
<P>
Israel so far refused to lift the total closure despite a
progress by the Palestinian National Authority (PNA) in fighting
againt terror and the improvement of security cooperation between
the two sides.
</P>
<P>
The same source told Xinhua that, someone tried to throw
molotov cocktails to a Jewish settler compound in Hebron, another
West Bank city about 50 kilometers south of Jerusalem, today, but
caused no damage to the compound and no one was injured.
</P>
<P>
Israeli police and troops rushed to the scene and conducted
questioning of the local residents and some arrests were made,
the source added. 
</P>
</TEXT>
