<HEADLINE> Veteran Sun Shuwei Wins Platform at National Games </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, October 11 (Xinhua) -- Former Olympic champion Sun
Shuwei of Guangdong province captured the men's 10-meter platform
gold medal at the Eighth National Games here Saturday night.
</P>
<P>
Sun, who won the same event at the 1992 Barcelona Olympic
Games, led all the way to take the gold with a total of 735.69
points.
</P>
<P>
However, the 21-year-old diving veteran failed to qualify for
the Centennial Olympic Games last year due to a slump form. He
made a strong comeback early this year by winning the gold in the
FINA Diving Grand Prix in Beijing.
</P>
<P>
Teeager Tian Liang, 18, of Shaanxi province, who beat Sun in
the qualifiers for the Atlanta Olympics, finished second with
721.35 points in spite of an event-high 96.90 points in his last
dive.
</P>
<P>
Xu Hao of Jiangsu province took the bronze medal with 675.54.
</P>
