<HEADLINE> Seven England Fans Arrested In Rome </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ROME, October 11 (Xinhua) -- Seven England fans were arrested
for attacking two Italian men on a train just hours before
Saturday's vital World Cup qualifier between Italy and England.
</P>
<P>
Italian news reports said some English fans ripped open the
door of the victims' compartment on a train from Milan to Rome,
which carried some 30 England fans, and began punching and kicking
a 63-year-old man and his son.
</P>
<P>
Police broke up the attack and handcuffed the seven fans to a
police station in Rome for booking when the train pulled into
Rome. Two police officers were slightly injured.
</P>
<P>
Five other arrests were reported in various incidents in the
early hours of Saturday for violence and resisting police officers.
</P>
<P>
English fans started pouring into the city on Friday and 10,000
were expected to arrive. They will be escorted by police directly
to Olympic stadium. 
