<HEADLINE> Macao International Music Festival Opens </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MACAO, October 11 (Xinhua) -- The 11th Macao International
Music Festival started here today featuring the theme on
commemoration of great musicians -- Franz Schubert and Johannes
Brahms.
</P>
<P>
While the annual music festival will mainly stage works of the
two great musicians, it will also show George Bizet's four-act
opera "Carmen," which will be co-performed by a dance troupe from
Spain, children's choir from a local school, the Shanghai
Philharmonic Choir and China's National Opera and Ballet Theater
Symphony Orchestra.
</P>
<P>
Officials of the Macao Cultural Department, which co-organized
the festival, said that the opera will be broadcast by a dozen
European broadcasting stations, including the BBC of England, HRK
of Norway, KDR of Denmark, SSR of Switzerland and RDP of Portugal.
</P>
<P>
During the half-month festival, a total of 17 performances will
be staged. Other programs include concert and Chinese folk song
and music nights.
</P>
<P>
The music festival is said to have gained increasing popularity
across the world. a large audience totaling more than 12,000 was
present at the performances last year. 
</P>
