<HEADLINE> 11th Asian Trade Promotion Forum to be Held in India </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW DELHI, October 11 (Xinhua)-- The 11th Asian Trade Promotion
Forum (ATPF) is scheduled to be held in Panaji, capital of Goa
State of western India, from October 13, official sources said
here today.
</P>
<P>
It is for the first time that the ATPF meeting will be held in
India. Participants in the two-day meeting are expected to
deliberate on trade promotion and developing closer cooperation in
the Asian-Pacific region. Around 35 delegates from 14 countries
and regions will participate in the meeting.
</P>
<P>
India has attached considerable importance to trade with ATPF
countries and regions including Australia, Japan, China, Hong
Kong, New Zealand and Singapore and they have accounted for 30.55
percent of India's exports in 1996-97 financial year (April 1,
1996-March 31, 1997), said Chairman and Managing Director of the
India Trade Promotion Organization (ITPO) K.K. Mathur on Friday.
</P>
<P>
India's exports to the Asian-Pacific region were to the tune of
10,114.42 million U.S. dollars in 1996-97, an increase of 2.24
percent over that in 1995-96.  
</P>
</TEXT>
