<TEXT>
<P>
MONTEVIDEO, October 11 (Xinhua) -- An Argentine domestic
airliner carrying 70 passengers and five crew members crashed near
a Uruguayan border town late Friday when trying to avoid a heavy
storm.
</P>
<P>
All passengers and crew members were feared dead in the crash
in a swampy area outside the Uruguayan town of Fray Bentos at
about 11 p.m. local time, the AFP reported from Buenos Aires,
quoting Argentine air force secretary general Juan Manuel Vasquez.
</P>
<P>
A witness told a Uruguayan television station that he saw a
ball of fire fell behind a hill and then a huge explosion.
</P>
<P>
The DC-9 of the Austral airlines were en route from Posada in
northeast Argentina to Buenos Aires when it disappeared from the
radar screen of air controllers at the Buenos Aires airport.
</P>
<P>
Rescue teams from both Uruaguay and Argentina rushed to the
crash site about 450 kilometers north of Buenos Aires, but there
were still no confirmed reports of casualties. 
</P>
