<HEADLINE> International Conference to Promote Population-Related Study </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, October 11 (Xinhua) -- The main theme of the 23rd
IUSSP General Population Conference scheduled to open here Sunday
is to arouse the scientists to make greater efforts in the
research of population science through the exchange of their
achievements and views in this field.
</P>
<P>
John C. Caldwell, President of the International Union
for the Scientific Study of Population (IUSSP), made the
remark here today.
</P>
<P>
He told a press conference that population growth, fertility,
mortality, reproductive health and the aging of population are the
subjects to be discussed during the six-day conference.
</P>
<P>
Founded in 1928, IUSSP is a prestigious international academic
organization in the field of population studies, and the
four-yearly conference is its most important activity.
</P>
<P>
It is the first time that China has been chosen as the venue of
the conference.
</P>
<P>
Caldwell said IUSSP has been very interested in China
since its population accounts for 22 percent of the world's
total, and great changes have taken place in its fertility,
mortality and life expectancy over the past few decades.
</P>
<P>
He said there is a significant number of Chinese members in the
IUSSP, and about 40 percent of the more than 1,300 participants in
the 23rd conference are from China. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
