<HEADLINE> Sight Restoration Program Initiated in Hunan </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CHANGSHA, October 11 (Xinhua) -- Sight First China Action, a
sight restoring program funded by the international charity, the
Lions Club, has been initiated in central China's Hunan province.
</P>
<P>
The first team of ophthalmologists left Wednesday this capital
city of Hunan for remote mountainous areas in the province to
perform sight restoration surgery on local cataract victims.
</P>
<P>
Over the next month, the doctors plan to perform cataract
removing surgery on more than 1,000 patients, and help train and
instruct local doctors.
</P>
<P>
According to an agreement signed between the Lions Club and the
China Disabled Persons Federation in August, the charity will
provide 15.3 million US dollars to China over the next five years,
to restore sight for more than 1.75 million cataract victims in
the country, especially those in remote and poverty-stricken areas.
</P>
<P>
Hunan province is one of major areas covered by Sight First
China Action program. Some 70,700 cataract removing operations are
planned from 1997 to 2001, with aid from the Lions Club. 
</P>
</TEXT>
