<DOCNO> XIE19971011.0147 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-10-11 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China Achieves Great in Sports from 1992 to 1997 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, October 11 (Xinhua) -- From 1992 to 1997, China has
reapt great achievements in sports in both international and
domestic arenas, from the development of sports industry to sports
exchange with other countries and regions.
</P>
<P>
Over the past five years, the Chinese athletes have won 448
world titles and set up 356 world records, accounting for 43 and
42 percents respectively of the totals achieved in the past 48
years after the founding of the People's Republic of China in
1949.
</P>
<P>
China remained firmly as a dominating sportspower in the
continent, topping the medals tally for the third consecutive time
in the Hiroshima Asian Games in 1994.
</P>
<P>
In the 1995 43rd World Table Tennis Championships, the Chinese
paddlers made a clean sweep of seven titles, a repetition of such
a feat first-ever achieved in 1981.
</P>
<P>
The Chinese athletes also displayed brilliant performances in
the 1992 and 1996 Olympic Games, garnering 16 golds twice and
finishing fourth on the gold tally each time.
</P>
<P>
China has also hosted 272 international competitions and 1,270
home meets, demostrating the increasing role it was playing in the
international sports community.
</P>
<P>
With the support of governments at all levels, sports
infrastructure also witnessed a rapid growth in the past five
years, up 12.28 percent annually.
</P>
<P>
So far, China boasts of 615,693 stadiums and gymnasiums of any
kind, with per capita coverage of sports facilites increased from
0.05 square meters in early 1950s to current 0.65.
</P>
<P>
All the sports facilities are opened to the pulic under the
stipulations of the State Physical Culture and Sports Commission.
</P>
<P>
From 1993 to 1996, China has issued sports lottery worthy of
2.2 billion yuans (260 million U.S. dollars), with 600 million
yuans (65 million U.S. dollars) alloted for the development of
sports, striding a concrete step for the market-oriented reforms.
</P>
<P>
In the past five years, sports exchanges with other countries
and regions have also been expanded considerably. China has
gained its memberships in 97 internaional sports organizations and
87 Asian sports federations, and estalished sports relations with
over 150 countries and regions.
</P>
<P>
During the five-year period, 268 Chinese have made their great
contributions after being elected to the key posts in 47
interntional federations and 52 Asian sports bodies.
</P>
<P>
The close ties with other countries and regions and the
international sports community help deepen the mutual
understanding and friendship between the Chinese people and the
peoples of the rest of the world, and also contributed great for
China's reform and opening-up policy. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
