<DATE_TIME> 1997-10-11 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Facts of Chinese National Games (2-last) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The Fourth National Games:
</P>
<P>
September 15-30, 1979, Beijing
</P>
<P>
Some 3,824 athletes from 31 delegations participated in the
games which featured 34 events.
</P>
<P>
The games posted five new world records and three world youth
records. And five world standards were equalled. The games also
witnessed 102 national records bettered.
</P>
<P>
The Fifth National Games:
</P>
<P>
September 18-October 1, 1993, Shanghai
</P>
<P>
The 25-sports games, which drew 8,943 athletes from 31
delegations, produced two world records and levelled three. Also
bettered at the games were a world youth record, four Asian
records and 60 national marks.
</P>
<P>
The Sixth National Games:
</P>
<P>
November 20-December 5, 1987, Guangzhou
</P>
<P>
The games, which featured 44 medal events and three exhibition
events, had an entry of 37 delegations with 6,766 athletes. A
total of 15 world records were improved with another three
equalled. The games also established 48 Asian records or bests, as
well as 82 national marks.
</P>
<P>
The Seventh National Games:
</P>
<P>
September 4-15, co-hosted by Beijing and Chengdu
</P>
<P>
A total of 7,481 athletes from 45 delegations took part in the
games, which offered 334 golds from 45 medal events. Four world
records were broken and another three tied. One hundred Asian
marks bettered or surpassed, and 117 national marks rewritten.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
