<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Facts of Chinese National Games (1) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, October 11 (Xinhua) -- Following are some facts about
the seven previous Chinese National Games:
</P>
<P>
The First National Games:
</P>
<P>
September 13-October 3, 1959, Beijing
</P>
<P>
The inaugural games featured 36 medal events and six exhibition
ones, registered an entry of 7,707 athletes from 29 delegations.
</P>
<P>
During the games, four world records fell in the men's 100m
breaststroke swimming, women's small-bore pistol shooting,
parachuting and radio-control air modelng. Besides, 106 new
national records were established.
</P>
<P>
The Second National Games:
</P>
<P>
September 11-28, 1965, Beijing
</P>
<P>
The 22-sport games, which attracted 7,395 athletes from 29
delegations, witnessed nine world records cracked in weightlifting,
shooting, archery and parachuting, and 130 national marks were
rewritten. Wushu, the Chinese martial arts, was the only
demonstration event in the games.
</P>
<P>
The Third National Games:
</P>
<P>
September 12-28, 1975, Beijing
</P>
<P>
The games had a participation of 31 delegations with 7,302
athletes. It featured 28 medal events including speed skating,
figure skating, ice hockey and skiing, the events first listed as
medals at the National Games.
</P>
<P>
Three world marks were rewritten and another two were levelled
during the games. Also established were 62 national records.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
