<HEADLINE> International Petroleum Exhibition Opens in Beijing </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, October 11 (Xinhua) -- The International Petroleum and
Petrochemical Exhibition '9 7 was inaugurated here today at the
China International Exhibition Center, drawing altogether 400
companies from 24 countries and regions.
</P>
<P>
Chinese vice-premier Wu Bangguo and Mr.Dirk van der Meer,
president of the World Petroleum Congress (WPC), cut the ribbon
at the opening ceremony.
</P>
<P>
Petroleum enterprises and companies from the US, Canada, Italy,
Argentina, Australia, France, Germany, UK, Saudi Arabia, Russia,
Japan and China are displaying at the exhibition their latest
technologies, techniques and equipment in the field of oil
exploration, extraction, refining and environmental protection.
</P>
<P>
All major Chinese oil companies are participating in
the exhibition, displaying their latest achievements in the
petroleum industry.
</P>
<P>
The exhibition covering 6,670 sq m., the largest ever in the
country's oil sector, is jointly sponsored by the China National
Petroleum Corp. (CNPC), China Petrochemical Corp. (Sinopec),
China National Offshore Oil Corp. (CNOOC), China National
Chemicals Import and Export Corp. (Sinochem) and China National
Star Petroleum Corp (CNSPC). 
