<HEADLINE> Foreign Investment up in Vietnam </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HANOI, October 11 (Xinhua) -- Foreign investment in Vietnam for
the past several months this year has been "on the rise" with 38
new projects under way, the "Vietnam News" reported today.
</P>
<P>
In the first 9 months of this year, Vietnam had 248 licensed
foreign projects with a total registered capital of 2.958 billion
dollars.
</P>
<P>
The number of licensed projects increased by 13 percent against
the same period of last year, while investment was 75 percent of
last year's figure, according to the English-language daily.
</P>
<P>
The total output value of businesses with foreign investment
totalled 1.75 billion dollars in the first nine months of this
year, up 44 percent against the same period last year. 
</P>
