<HEADLINE> Cooperation Between Portugal, China on Macao Beneficial </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LISBON, October 10 (Xinhua) -- Portugal's President Jorge
Sampaio said that the cooperation on the Sino-Portuguese Joint
Declaration is productive, and the successful settlement of the
Macao issue will be a good beginning for future cooperation.
</P>
<P>
Sampaio made the remarks during his meeting with Chen Mingshu,
deputy procurator-general of the Chinese Supreme People's
Procuratorate, who arrived here on October 6 for an official visit
to Portugal.
</P>
<P>
Sampaio said that he is optimistic about the future of the
Portugal-China ties, adding that the two countries should further
enhance cooperation according to the Joint Declaration signed on
April 13, 1987.
</P>
<P>
According to the declaration, China will assume the exercise of
sovereignty over Macao on December 20, 1999.
</P>
<P>
As a member state of the European Union (EU), Sampaio said his
country would play an important role in promoting cooperation
between the EU countries and China. 
</P>
