<DOCNO> XIE19971011.0168 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-10-11 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Food Situation in Iraq Needs to Improve: UN Food Mission </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ROME, October 10 (Xinhua) -- Malnutrition is still a serious
problem among the people throughout Iraq, although there has been
an improvement in the food supply following the implementation of
the UN resolution to allow Iraq to sell oil for food.
</P>
<P>
According to the latest joint assessment mission by the United
Nations Food and Agriculture Organization and the World Food
Program, "There is considerable evidence of widespread
malnutrition, and the quality, availability and nutritional value
of food in the country" is inadequate. "Supply shortages have been
experienced over the last seven years.
</P>
<P>
"The need for vulnerable group feeding remains essential. The
SCR 986 (UN Security Council Resolution No. 986) basket does not
meet the special nutritional food needs of vulnerable groups, such
as malnourished children," the joint mission said.
</P>
<P>
Financial sanctions have been imposed on Iraq by the UN since the
end of the Gulf War in 1991.
</P>
<P>
However, under the UN's recent oil-for-food resolution, which
has permitted Iraq to export limited quantities of oil since 1996
to finance imports of food and other humanitarian needs, Iraq has
sold two billion U.S. dollars worth of oil in the first six months.
</P>
<P>
On June 8, 1997, the UN Security Council extended the
resolution to include the second half year. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19971011.0169 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-10-11 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> U.N. Convention Against Desertification Ends in Rome </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ROME, October 10 (Xinhua) -- Ministers and other senior
officials from 122 countries ended a two-week meeting here this
afternoon on the U.N. Convention to combat desertification.
</P>
<P>
The purpose of the new approach is to establish a "Global
Mechanism" for promoting international support to help return the
world's dry lands to economic and environmental health, and to
promote the transfer of financial an technological assistance.
</P>
<P>
This mechanism will help insure that every country which needs
international support will have full access to information about
multilateral and bilateral sources. In this way, it will act as a
catalyst to improve coordination, minimize overlaps and share
information, ideas and success.
</P>
<P>
The participants of the meeting have agreed to establish a
permanent secretariat to replace the current interim one and also
agreed on a 1999 work plan and budget for the secretariat.
</P>
<P>
The next meeting will be held in late 1998 in Dakar, Senegal.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
