<HEADLINE> Krajisnik Opposes Karadzic's Arrest </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BELGRADE, October 10 (Xinhua) -- Momcilo Krajisnik, a member of
the Presidency of Bosnia, said today that it would be "a
disastrous mistake" if the international community demanded the
arrest of former Bosnian Serb leader Radovan Karadzic.
</P>
<P>
"It would be a disastrous mistake if the international
community does so, for it will stir up strong opposition from the
Serbs and threaten the Dayton peace accord," Krajisnik said while
talking to the newspaper Nedeljni Dnevnik in Novi Sad, the capital
city of Vojvodina Province in Yugoslavia.
</P>
<P>
Karadzic, who is regarded as a war hero by the Bosnian Serbs,
was put on the list of war criminals by the international tribunal
at the Hague after the three-and-a-half-year war ended in December
1995, in accordance with the Dayton peace accord signed in the
United States. 
</P>
