<HEADLINE> Backgrounder: China to Double Natural Gas Production in 2005 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, October 11 (Xinhua) -- (Editor's Notes: The 15th World
Petroleum Congress is to open in Beijing tomorrow. Xinhua News
Agency is expected to release a series of backgrounders to outline
the development of China's petroleum industry as of today.)
</P>
<P>
China plans to double its annual natural gas production
capacity to 30 billion cubic meters by the year 2005.
</P>
<P>
The country is expected to verify additional onshore gas
reserves of one trillion cubic meters by the end of the century,
with the aggregated total hitting two trillion cubic meters.
</P>
<P>
By 2000, China's gas production capacity will rise by another
10 billion cubic meters, with the total topping 25 billion cubic
meters.
</P>
<P>
The gas production of the country last year totaled 19,041
million cubic meters.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
