<DATE_TIME> 1997-10-11 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Train Collision Kills 11 in Southwest Bangladesh </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DHAKA, October 11 (Xinhua) -- At least eleven people were
killed and over thirty injured when an express train on Friday
rammed a stone-laden freight train at Singair Station, twelve
miles off Jessore town in southwest Bangladesh, said reports
reaching here today.
</P>
<P>
Police recovered mangled bodies from a twisted carriage of the
Rocket Express train which derailed with the engine in the
accident. The injured were rushed to hospitals in Jessore and
Khulna town, where at least 22 were admitted with serious wounds.
</P>
<P>
Witness said, the Rocket, on its way to Parbatipur from Khulna,
crashed on the engine of the stationary freight train, reportedly
ignoring red flags, raised to warn against danger as some wagons
of the goods train had derailed on the same track earlier.
</P>
<P>
The authorities immediately suspended the driver, assistant
driver and guard of the Rocket Express, said a press release
issued by the Communication Ministry.
</P>
<P>
A three-member high-powered inquiry committee has been formed
to probe the causes of the accident and identify the persons
responsible for it, the press release said.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, Prime Minister Sheikh Hasina on Friday expressed her
profound shock at the loss of lives in the train accident and
instructed the authorities to take all measures for the treatment
of the injured persons.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
