<HEADLINE> 12 More Dengue Cases Reported in New Delhi </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW DELHI, October 11 (Xinhua) -- With 12 more dengue cases
being reported on Friday, the total number of patients have
increased to 164, local English newspaper the Hindustan Times said
here today.
</P>
<P>
Two deaths have already taken place in the city due to dengue.
Last year the deadly dengue virus had claimed 423 lives in the
capital.
</P>
<P>
The majority of these deaths took place during the month of
October when the dengue-carrying aedes mosquito breeds the most.
Doctors have again warned that any patient with a fever should be
rushed to hospital immediately.  
