<HEADLINE> Backgrounder: China's Oil Output to Reach 200 Million Tons in 2010 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, October 11 (Xinhua) -- (Editor's Notes: The 15th World
Petroleum Congress is to open in Beijing tomorrow. Xinhua News
Agency is expected to release a series of backgrounders to outline
the development of China's petroleum industry as of today.)
</P>
<P>
China's oil production is set to reach 200 million tons in the
year 2010.
</P>
