<HEADLINE> Brief Latin American Cultural News (1) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MEXICO CITY, October 10 (Xinhua) -- The following are news
briefs about recent cultural events in Latin American countries:
</P>
<P>
Argentine Film Wins Prize in Norway
</P>
<P>
BUENOS AIRES -- The Argentine film "Sol de Otono," directed by
Eduardo Mignogna, won the "Premio del Publico" award at a cinema
festival that ended last week in Oslo, Norway.
</P>
<P>
"Sol de Otono," a love story between two people 50 years old, had won
the best film reward in the 37th Festival of Cine and TV of
Cartagena, Colombia.
</P>
<P>
The movie has also won many top prizes in Argentina.
</P>
<P>
Mercosur Holds its First Biennial Arts Exhibit
</P>
<P>
BRASILIA -- The First Southern Common Market (Mercosur) Visual
Arts Exhibition is being held October 2 to November 30 in Porto
Alegre of Brazil.
</P>
<P>
The exhibition, aimed at promoting visual art in the Mercosur
member countries, has drawn 800 works from seven Latin American
countries.
</P>
<P>
Brazil Government Helps Develop Musical Bands
</P>
<P>
BRASILIA -- The Brazilian Culture Ministry decided to invest
1.5 million dollars in a program aimed at developing the country's
musical bands.
</P>
<P>
Through the program, which is called "Support to Music Bands",
a total of 123 Brazilian bands will receive more than 2,000
new musical instruments at the end of this year.
</P>
<P>
Blues Festival To Be Held in Montevideo
</P>
<P>
MONTEVIDEO -- The "Montevideo Blues Festival" will be held
October 11 in the Uruguayan capital.
</P>
<P>
Many famous artists will attend the festival, including Katie
Webster, The Vasti Group, the Mississippi Blues Band, and Big
Blues Band. 
</P>
