<HEADLINE> Brief Latin American Cultural News (2) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANAGUA -- Young people from 14 Latin American countries will
hold a cultural convention in Managua on November 15, which will
include dancing, musical performances and costume exhibitions.
</P>
<P>
The festival aims to deliver a message of peace in Nicaragua
and rescue the moral and spiritual values of Nicaraguan youth.
</P>
<P>
SANTAFE DE BOGOTA -- Colombian singer and song writer Shakira
will hold a concert in her country after having left her country
20 months ago. Profits from the concert will be donated to several
foundations to help protect the less fortunate children.
</P>
<P>
The artist will complete her scheduled 90 concerts in 20
countries in two years. She has sold three million copies of her
record "Bare Feet."
</P>
<P>
Shakira is only surpassed, at a Hispano-American level, by
Spanish artist Enrique Iglesias who sold four million copies of
his first album. 
</P>
