<HEADLINE> Andean Community, EU to Start Dialogue </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LIMA, October 10 (Xinhua) -- The Andean Community and the
European Union (EU) will begin political discussions with members
of the European Community (EU) next week, Ecuadoran President
Fabian Alarcon said today.
</P>
<P>
Alarcon, also chairman of the Andean Presidential Council, will
visit Belgium and Luxembourg. He will be accompanied by foreign
ministers from the Andean countries, the Andean Community general
secretary and the president of the Andean Promotion Corporation.
</P>
<P>
The Andean Community authorities will hold a political dialogue
on October 15-17 with European Commission President Jacques Santer
and Vice-President Manuel Marin respectively, and EU Council
President Jean-Claude Juncker.
</P>
<P>
European Parliament President Jose Maria Gil Rlbles and the
members of the parliament foreign policy commission will also
attend the meetings.
</P>
<P>
The political dialogue was endorsed by the top representatives
of the two blocs in Rome through a joint declaration signed in
June 1996. 
</P>
</TEXT>
