<HEADLINE> Special Stamp Albums to Be Auctioned Marking National Games </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, October 11 (Xinhua) -- A Shanghai auctioneer will
sell six special stamp albums to mark China's Eighth National
Games which open on October 12.
</P>
<P>
The albums contain stamps, commemorative envelopes, and
postcards issued for the First National Games of 1959, several of
which are valuable for collectors.
</P>
<P>
In addition, the albums contain the signatures of stamp
designers, gold medal winners at Chinese or international
tournaments and heads of the State Physical Culture and Sports
Commission.
</P>
<P>
The auction will be held on October 12 in the Shanghai
Exhibition Center. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
