<HEADLINE> Rusedski Beats Martin in CA Trophy ATP Tour </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
VIENNA, October 10 (Xinhua) -- Greg Rusedski thrashed American
Todd Martin in the quarter-finals of the CA Trophy ATP Tour event.
</P>
<P>
The fourth-seed, who this week rose to No.4 in the world
rankings, won 6-1, 6-7 (5/7), 6-3 to set up an all-British
semi-final against Tim Henman.
</P>
<P>
Henman, who has won his three previous meetings with Rusedski,
earlier booked his place in the semis with a 6-4, 6-1 defeat of
Slovakian Karol Kucera.
</P>
<P>
Canadian-born Rusedski, who hasn't dropped serve this week,
reached his fourth successive semi-final with a win in 1 hour 42
minutes.
</P>
<P>
Rusedski said he was not excited about facing Henman and was
more concerned about qualifying for the year-ending ATP Tour
Championships.
</P>
<P>
"As far as tomorrow goes, it will be just another match,
although an important one on the road to Hannover which is my
goal," he said.
</P>
<P>
"But it was a good win for me today, especially as it was the
first time I have beaten Todd."
</P>
<P>
Henman was faster than Rusedski in his quarter, taking just 63
minutes to overwhelm Kucera.
</P>
<P>
Henman reached the semis for the second straight week. He lost
to Australian Mark Philippoussis in the last four in Basle,
Switzerland, last week.
</P>
<P>
Third-seed Goran Ivanisevic of Croatia continued his recent
renaissance with a 7-6 (7/2), 3-6, 6-3 win over Bohdan Ulihrach
of the Czech Republic in his quarter.
</P>
<P>
He will now play former Wimbledon champion Richard Krajicek of
the Netherlands who beat Sweden's Magnus Larsson 6-4, 6-4. 
</P>
</TEXT>
