<HEADLINE> Hingis Breezes into Semis of WTA Tour </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BONN, October 10 (Xinhua) -- World number one Martina Hingis of
Switzerland outclassed Bulgaria's Magdalena Maleeva with a 6-2,
6-3 victory and stepped into the semi-finals of the Filderstadt
WTA Tour event on Friday.
</P>
<P>
The Swiss teenager will play against fifth-seeded South African
Amanda Coetzer as Coetzer eliminated another Swiss Patty Schnyder,
6-2, 7-5 in her quarter-final.
</P>
<P>
Coetzer contributed the third upset of the season to Hingis
three weeks ago in Liepzig, Germany, winning 6-4, 4-6, 7-6 (7/3)
in the semis.
</P>
<P>
Hingis' other defeats came in the French Open final against
Croatian Iva Majoli in early June and in Los Angeles in August by
American Lindsay Davenport.
</P>
<P>
In other quarters played Friday, eighth-seeded Irina Spirlea of
Romania ousted Arantxa Sanchez of Spain 7/5, 6/4 and unseeded
American Lisa Raymond routed Japan's Naoko Sawamatsu 6-2, 6-3.
</P>
