<HEADLINE> Russia Has Fewer Criminal Cases in First Nine Months </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW, October 10 (Xinhua) -- Russian Deputy Prime Minister
and Interior Minister Anatoly Kulikov said today that the overall
rate of crime in Russia in the first nine months of this year
dropped by 9.1 percent compared with that of the same period last
year.
</P>
<P>
However, the cases involving drugs increased by 80 percent to
131,000, which is a "disastrous number," Kulikov told reporters at
a news conference.
</P>
<P>
The rate of crime in most parts of Russia has been lowered, but
the number of murder cases has increased.
</P>
<P>
Police have solved 1.253 million out of 1.8 million cases in
the country between January and September, Kulikov added. 
</P>
</TEXT>
