<HEADLINE> Panama To Release More Than 1,000 Prison Inmates </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PANAMA CITY, October 10 (Xinhua) -- The Panamanian penitentiary
system will release more than 1,000 national and foreign inmates
due to a reform to the justice codex being promoted by the
Panamanian government.
</P>
<P>
This reform would permit, according to an official report, to
release 628 Panamanian inmates, and 414 foreigners who serve
condemns in several prisons of the country would be deported to
their respective countries.
</P>
<P>
This proposal, presented by the Panamanian government to the
plenum of the Legislative Assembly, will benefit the inmates who
have fulfilled the maximum penalty the law prescribes for the
crime they are accused.
</P>
<P>
After an intense discussion of several days, the new law was
passed last night in the third debate by the plenum of the
Legislative Assembly, and now must be approved by the President of
the Republic for its promulgation.
</P>
<P>
Despite the positive effects of this law project for the
administration of justice and on the Panamanian penitentiary
system, there were voices of protest, among them the Panamanian
College of Lawyers, which has asked President Ernesto Perez
Balladares not to approve the project. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
