<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Rodman Signs with Bulls </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, October 10 (Xinhua) -- Dennis Rodman, the National
Basketball Association rebounding king for the past six years,
signed a one-year contract with to the reigning champion Chicago
Bulls on Friday.
</P>
<P>
The deal, contingent upon a physical examination, means Rodman
could be in uniform for an exhibition game Saturday and at the
McDonalds Championship, an international club championship set
for next week in Paris.
</P>
<P>
Rodman, who made nine million dollars last season, will be paid
four million dollars with clauses that could boost his salary
near previous levels, provided he does not suffer injuries and
suspensions.
</P>
<P>
Rodman was not available for Chicago's first exhibition game
against Seattle on Friday but could play when the Bulls and
SuperSonics meet on Saturday in Lawrence, Kansas.
</P>
<P>
The Bulls will be without their other starting forward, Scottie
Pippen, for up to three months after he underwent left foot
surgery last Monday.
</P>
<P>
Rodman, 36, is best known for controversial kicking and
head-butting as well as a rainbow of hair dyes. Last season the
Bulls suspended Rodman for two games and the league banished him
for 12 games, 11 for kicking a cameraman and one for a scuffle
with a rival player.
</P>
<P>
A sprained knee sidelined him for the final month of the
season, but Rodman still won the NBA rebounding title with 16.1 a
game over 55 contests. In the playoffs his average slid to 8.4
rebounds. 
</P>
</TEXT>
