<HEADLINE> Beijing Newspaper Highlights </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, October 11 (Xinhua) -- Highlights of today's major
Beijing-based newspapers are as follows:
</P>
<P>
 People's Daily
</P>
<P>
-- People's Daily, China's leading national newspaper, carried
an editorial today, hailing the forthcoming 15th World Petroleum
Congress and extending a warm welcome to friends from throughout
the world.
</P>
<P>
The fact that the congress, the first of its kind to be held in
a developing country, will be held in China indicates the
increasing strength and rising international status of the
nation's petroleum industry, the paper said.
</P>
<P>
-- The State Council, China's cabinet, issued a circular
yesterday ordering a nationwide audit of taxation and pricing
activities, as well as other types of enterprise financial
activities, during 1996 and 1997.
</P>
<P>
 Xinhua Daily Telegraph
</P>
<P>
-- Chinese President Jiang Zemin met with W Allen,
chairman and CEO of Phillips Petroleum Company of the United
States, and other members of the board of the company yesterday.
</P>
<P>
Jiang said the Chinese government welcomes and supports the
cooperation between US businesses and Chinese firms.
</P>
<P>
-- Preparations have been completed for the 15th World
Petroleum Congress (WPC) scheduled for October 12-16 in Beijing,
which is expected to draw 4,300 representatives from 88 countries.
</P>
<P>
China Daily
</P>
<P>
-- China will double its efforts to ease the country's
transportation bottlenecks within the remaining years of this
century, the State Planning Commission said yesterday in Beijing.
</P>
<P>
-- China is to launch three more satellites within the year,
including one telecommunications satellite and two iridium
satellites, said Wang Liheng, vice-president of China Aerospace
Corporation, in Beijing yesterday.
</P>
<P>
-- It was the ninth day of the ninth lunar month again
yesterday -- a traditional Chinese festival for the elderly. Apart
from the pleasure they enjoy each year -- mountaineering, they are
receiving more care from society. 
</P>
