<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Cho Wins 78kg Gold in World Judo Championships </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, October 10 (Xinhua) -- The Atlanta bronze medallist and
East Asian champion Cho In-Chu of South Korea defeated Djamel
Bouras of France to win the 78kg category title at the World Judo
Championships on Friday.
</P>
<P>
Cho, the winner of the Paris tournament early this year, scored
an excllent ippon victory over Frenchman Bouras for the second
time, giving South Korea the second gold of the day. 
</P>
</TEXT>
