<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Brazilian Coffee Exports Soar </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
RIO DE JANEIRO, October 10 (Xinhua) -- Brazilian green coffee
exports increased 96.3 percent in value and 43.4 percent in volume
during the first nine months of this year, compared to the same
period of 1996.
</P>
<P>
Coffee sales abroad earned during the period 2.050 billion
dollars and a volume of 10.9 million 60-kilo bags, according to
the Brazilian Coffee Exporters Federation (Febec) today.
</P>
<P>
September coffee exports increased 72.2 percent in value and
nine percent in volume in comparison to the same month of 1996.
</P>
<P>
September sales abroad rose to 244.2 million dollars and 1.2
million bags. 
</P>
</TEXT>
