<HEADLINE> U.S. Dollar Falls Against yen </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW YORK, October 10 (Xinhua) -- The U.S. dollar fell to a
seven-week low against the Japanese yen Friday in New York but
rose against the German mark.
</P>
<P>
In late New York trading, the dollar was quoted at 119.78 yen,
down from 121.10 late Thursday and its lowest level since August
28. The U.S. currency also settled at 1.7486 marks, up from
1.7439.
</P>
<P>
The German currency fell 1.5 percent against the yen Friday,
pulling the dollar lower against the yen but boosting it against
the mark. The German central bank raise interest Thursday, the
first move in five years.
</P>
<P>
Central banks in France, Belgium, Holland and Denmark followed
the German bank's move Thursday.
</P>
<P>
Other late dollar rates in New York, compared with late
Thursday: 1.4537 Swiss francs, down from 1.4560; 5.8685 French
francs, up from 5.8591; 1,719.25 Italian lire, up from 1,717.00;
and 1.3787 Canadian dollars, up from 1.3742.
</P>
<P>
The British pound was quoted at 1.6223 U.S. dollars, down from
1.6244 U.S. dollars. 
</P>
</TEXT>
