<HEADLINE> Ashrawi Urges U.S. to Be Evenhanded in Mideast </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, October 10 (Xinhua) -- A senior Palestinian
official on Friday urged the United States to be evenhanded in its
mediation for resolving disputes between Israel and the
Palestinians.
</P>
<P>
Hanan Ashrawi, the higher education minister of the Palestinian
Authority, told a gathering sponsored by the Arab-American Forum
that Washington should adopt a "more evenhanded position" and end
its habit of constantly embracing the Israeli position.
</P>
<P>
She deplored what she called the steady erosion of U.S.
opposition to Israeli settlement activity.
</P>
<P>
Whereas the United States used to call the Israeli settlement
activity illegal, it is now reduced to seeking a "temporary pause"
or a "time-out" in settlement construction, she said.
</P>
<P>
Ashrawi said the peace process has been faltering because
Israel and the United States have been attaching disproportionate
attention to Israeli security while neglecting other components of
the peace process.
</P>
<P>
U.S. officials pay little heed to Palestinian security, which
is "being trampled daily" by Israeli occupiers, she said.
</P>
<P>
As a result, the peace process is being plagued by "cycles of
crises and cycles of erosion of confidence," she added 
</P>
