<HEADLINE> Ethiopia Pledges to Further Ties With France </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ADDIS ABABA, October 10 (Xinhua) -- Ethiopian Prime Minister
Meles Zenawi today held talks with visiting French Foreign
Minister Hubert Vedrine on bilateral issues and situation in the
central African region.
</P>
<P>
According to a report from the Ethiopian News Agency, during
the meeting, Meles stressed the importance for the international
community to consider historical aspects of the crises in the
region whenever taking measures to resolve the conflict in the
area.
</P>
<P>
Ethiopia, he said, seeks to further strengthen its ties with
France and engage in cooperation based on the mutual interest of
the two countries.
</P>
<P>
The French foreign minister echoed by saying that his country
attaches great importance to its relations with Ethiopia.
</P>
<P>
His visit, Vedrine noted, is part of a new approach by the
French government to strengthen ties with African countries,
especially with those countries which had no traditionally
amicable relations with France.
</P>
<P>
Vedrine also met with his Ethiopian counterpart Seyoum Mesfin
today on bilateral and regional issues. 
</P>
</TEXT>
