<TEXT>
<P>
ANKARA, October 10 (Xinhua) -- Turkish Deputy Prime Minister
Bulent Ecevit will visit Sweden and Finland from October 13 to 16
to seek support for his country's bid for European Union (EU)
membership.
</P>
<P>
The semi-official Anatolia News Agency said today Ecevit is
expected to meet Swedish Prime Minister Goran Persson in Stockholm
and Finnish Premier Paavo Lipponen in Helsinki.
</P>
