<HEADLINE> Sir Leon Brittan to Visit China on WTO Accession </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BRUSSELS, October 10 (Xinhua) -- Sir Leon Brittan,
vice-president of the European Commission, next week will visit
China for talks on China's accession to the World Trade
Organization (WTO), it was learned here today.
</P>
<P>
Another mission of Sir Leon's four-day visit to Beijing,
beginning from Monday, would be to develop plans for the future
expansion of the European Union (EU)'s cooperation program in
China, according to a communique issued by the Commission, the
EU's executive arm, Friday in Brussels.
</P>
<P>
Sir Leon is scheduled to hold meetings with Chinese
Vice-Premier Zhu Rongji, Chinese Foreign Minister Qian Qichen and
Wu Yi, Chinese minister of foreign trade and economic cooperation.
</P>
<P>
His visit to Beijing will also include the signing of a
memorandum of understanding on the future of the EU-China
cooperation program and the launch of a number of concrete
projects in areas such as environmental protection and training of
young European business managers in Chinese business practices.
</P>
</TEXT>
