<HEADLINE> Ogata to Continue Her Capacity as High Commissioner </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
UNITED NATIONS, October 10 (Xinhua) -- Ms. Sagako Ogata of
Japan would continue her capacity as High Commissioner for
Refugees, said a statement issued today by the spokesman's office.
</P>
<P>
The statement said that UN Secretary-General Kofi Annan
considered that Ms. Ogata, the UN High Commissioner for Refugees,
was an outstanding leader and that she would have made a fine
Deputy Secretary-General subject to the General Assembly' approval
of the post.
</P>
<P>
The statement said the UN chief and Ms. Ogata had discussed the
possibility of her taking up the position. However, given the
numerous and grave refugee crises with which Ms. Ogata was
dealing, she and the Secretary-General had mutually agreed that it
would be best for her to continue serving the international
community in her capacity as High Commissioner for refugees.
</P>
<P>
Ms. Ogata said that she was honored that the Secretary-General
had considered her for the important post of Deputy
Secretary-General. she was pleased that in her capacity as High
Commissioner for Refugees, she could continue to concentrate on
the many daunting humanitarian challenges. 
</P>
</TEXT>
